C 31 march 1682 183
hB
I wrott you on the 24 cur. what was needfull, sence recd yd of 25 d. as to the bustyns
of John vale, I doubt are not well, for though I desired him to provide for the bill of
N.C. of 33 curtt yett that is protisted, & though I bee vere much straightned have payd itt for
hi thenour, butt what remedu for that whih hell dew yeasterday, & must be payd 5 pa
whin £200 more of mj acceptance is to be payd: J.V. doth promise faixly yett not
onely H.C. his bills are protested, butt mony more, & for mee to draw on london
lookes not well, for utler att Epon, sampson r mathew randall att london beeng
broake will give litte creditt to young heoples drawing, there fore I will by no incane
medele with itt, nevers heless, how shall I secure S.C, I muyt step to Brussel
mij self, & gett from him what I can, or elce I must depend upon lus promise pray
lett mee know & first what I might draw on you for acctt of 3:6. to help him over
the sile, for I am strarghtned on all sides att no rate, & our standing out debts prove
vere slow, I am almost att miy witts end to redder my self in a lapacitie against what
Rows apeare, so I must excep in as much I can, deare freind you are not att all consihs
how I am in this world: pray a word if you do incline to allow mee somesing
reasonable for what is in yd handes, & in what time I might dispose
of itt, father egan hath payd mee the twente crownes which are past
to yd creditt, I want yd advise att large in boath concernes & assistancy
London m Benry Maynard
3 apli 1682
on the 25th past wrott you the needfull, sence recd. yd. of 13d. as to the bill of £229:1:2
onmichel, the first is in handes of Johr maseall iunor, which please to demand
& proeurs the valew where dew. I have the patt. & invoyce of goods ready provided which
I hope will give content white here, I exspect the drap & other cullours in spanish
clrathes desired: upon the new of french resiring from supembourg have sold a good parcell
of goods, & want them all ready shipt so take the lest of or tmite of providing good
drapeuliours as desired, butt ship not to many goods in one bottom, I could wish
the CN serer marckere, si god send ben clanck speedly over, I k.is a greas knave
& I Berseave they do all they can to beat in out of them goods, yett I would
have you not desist till you have them mentioned & pou. 25 or 30 piecers
a yeare, towards which all yd in drustry must be imployed, & then wee will
see if they shall not sume to acctt for if you, & I be satisfyed, what have
wee to do with others: & beconfident of my care & indeavour to do the best
god send Pindar speedly over, custumens coming in I can not in large
